---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1 style="margin: 22px 0 8px;">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="small">Last updated: {updated}</p>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 14px;">
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>CodeToCall</strong> ("we", "us") handles information when you use
      <a href="https://codetocall.com">codetocall.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not ask you to create an account.</li>
      <li>We do not collect phone numbers you type into the dial builder on our servers (the builder runs in your browser).</li>
      <li>We may display ads via Google AdSense. Ad providers may use cookies or similar technologies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
    <p>
      We use Google AdSense to display advertisements. AdSense may collect and use information about your visits to this and
      other websites to provide advertising. This may include the use of cookies, device identifiers, and similar technologies.
    </p>
    <p>
      We intend to request <strong>non-personalized ads</strong> where available. Non-personalized ads are not based on your
      past browsing behavior, but they may still use contextual information (like page content) and limited signals.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learn more about how Google uses information:
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="nofollow">https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We may use basic, privacy-respecting analytics in the future to understand which pages are useful.
      If we do, we will update this policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this policy, contact us at:
      <a href="mailto:jon.brady96@gmail.com">jon.brady96@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
